         It depends on what you are doing.  In many cases I would opt for the FT3 over the 65 HP/mana necklace.  However, I would max HP before lifeburning.</P><P>My whole theory revolves around mana management.  HP gives you more buffer to manage when liching.  But FT3 gives you free mana that otherwise you would not have.  300 mana every 10 minutes could be what allows you to kill that extra mob in a cycle.  And adding manaskin, would give you 400 mana (total) every 10 minutes.  And adding earring of solstice would give you 500 mana (total) every 10 minutes.</P><P>If you are a necro who gets beat on quite a bit and do not find yourself running low on mana, then I would recommend keeping the HP/Mana necklace.</P><P>I just got a FT1 1hb item from Griegs.  There will be times on raids that I use it instead of my epic.  It all adds up.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157918" target=new>Ishtarra Gemeinseele </a><BR>Warlock of the Dirty Soul<BR>Uber N00b Extraordinaire<BR>Tunare Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
