         This same question came up on my guild's board, I'll tell ye the same thing I told them :)</P><P>I only see this as useful for magicians, as they have poor mana regeneration capability. Flowing Thought is hugely overrated, especially when compared to what Arch Lich can do. </P><P>In 60 seconds, Flowing Thought 3 will regenerate 30 mana, while Arch Lich will regenerate 350 mana, at the cost of 530 hit points. Compare the FT3 neck to a black sapphire/velium neck (65 mana/hps), and the sapphire neck provides an extra 5 mana more in a single tick than the FT 3 neck provides in ten, with change...in another minute, follow with a Vexing, and we're back to full health, with ~200 mana to spare.</P><P>**Edit: That's not even taking into account regeneration buffs or items, which make AL even more efficient.</P><P>Obviously the neck would be a bit better for casting classes with lesser mana regen abilities, but even so, that's sacrificing a lot of stats for a piddly amount of mana.</P><P>I'm guessing/hoping this is the beginning of a nicer quest reward.</P><P><BR>[url=<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113749" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113749</a>][img]<a href="http://files.triton.net/dstevens/coldsig.gif" target="_blank">http://files.triton.net/dstevens/coldsig.gif</a>[/img][/url]</P><P><BR>Edited by - Delbin on 07/18/2002  13:11:05<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
