         FTx items give you mana per tick equal to x.  So FT3 gives 3 mana per tick.  One tick is 6 seconds.  10 ticks per minute.  I just threw out 10 minutes.  In reality, many camp cycles are 15 to 20 minutes.  If I said you get 30 mana per minute from FT3...that sounds like not much.  But 300 mana sounds like a respectable amount.  Hence I chose the longer time frame.  But, it does illustrate the reality that FT items may allow you to add an additional mob to your cycle.</P><P>Delbin...the flaw in your logic is that you assume HP are mana.  HP are not mana and do not equal mana regeneration.  HP items allow you to manage your HP more easily while in lich/archlich forms.  HP also save you from getting low HP aggro when managing your HP.  HP also lets you survive when getting summoned and pounded by boss mobs.  But plus HP items do not allow Arch lich to provide you with any more mana per tick than not having them. </P><P>Also, you do not take into account the PVP damage modifier we all enjoy with lich, making it cause us less damage than you state.</P><P>FT items are free mana that stack with all lich forms.  There is no FT versus Lich.  They are not mutually exclusive.  They work together.</P><P>Anc...I think it is part of the protect the gnome quest in CT, but not sure.  After I finish getting my guild equipt with Earrings of Solstice, we are going to rape CT.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157918" target=new>Ishtarra Gemeinseele </a><BR>Warlock of the Dirty Soul<BR>Uber N00b Extraordinaire<BR>Tunare Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
