        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=50638&amp;TOPIC_ID=6161&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Which+is+greater+FT3%3F+or+HP%2FMana&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         FT is nice.  As long as you have enough hps to use (arch demi whatever) lich comfortably with the mobs you kill then I wouldn't hesitate switching out HP gear for items that increase your effeciency (FT and focus items).  I aquired mana preservation affliction effeciency and recently got up to FT 5 and i can tell a large difference in what I can accomplish per hour.  And, even though I lost some hps with the gear switches I still lich 100percent of the time fighting.  So I am only increasing my mana regain and decreasing mana spent per spell.  And the best part of FT for a necro has yet to be mentioned or i missed it.  It allows you to regain mana while Feign death.  When the shit hits the fan and you gotta equip a zland heart and wait for a safe opportunity it is nice to also be regaining some mana.  Thats just my opinion.</P><P>Zorlak<BR>Tunare<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=225999" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=225999</a></P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
